The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 25 February is 225,017 (25,934.5 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 20 February, there were 5,877 new confirmed cases (677.4 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 13 February, there were 7,415 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 21% (1,538 fewer cases).
